Variation.
Forewing with a broad dorsal band before the middle, almost truncate at the apex, and a dorsal spot beyond it rectangular (
Fig. 68
), or a broad dorsal band bluntly oblique at the apex and a dorsal spot beyond it widened towards the costa (
Fig. 69
); the latter form matching the 
holotype
(
Friese & Moriuti 1968
).
